          {
            "@type": "@builder.io/sdk:Element",
            "@version": 2,
            "id": "builder-0fdda86cecbc4d559f531037a66ff935",
            "component": {
              "name": "Copy",
              "options": {
                "rawHtml": "<p>Other limitations include:</p><ul><li>Each account referenced may be at most 12,000,000 compute units used per block.</li><li>Instructions can only be called at a depth of 4 before the transaction reverts.</li></ul>"
              }
            },
            "responsiveStyles": {
              "large": {
                "display": "flex",
                "flexDirection": "column",
                "position": "relative",
                "flexShrink": "0",
                "boxSizing": "border-box",
                "marginTop": "20px"
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "@builder.io/sdk:Element",
            "@version": 2,
            "id": "builder-05c1836bbfb342b3be2fd20519c49165",
            "component": {
              "name": "Copy",
              "options": {
                "rawHtml": "<h2>Mempool</h2><p>Unlike Ethereum, Solana does not have mempools. Solana validators instead <a href=\"https://solana.com/docs/core/transactions/retry#:~:text=The%20Journey%20of%20a%20Transaction%20%23\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">forward all transactions</a> to up to four leaders on the leader schedule. Not having a mempool forces the transactions to hop from leader to leader until blockhash expiration, but it also reduces the overhead of gossip across the cluster.</p>"
              }
            },
            "responsiveStyles": {
              "large": {
                "display": "flex",
                "flexDirection": "column",
                "position": "relative",
                "flexShrink": "0",
