            "id": "builder-776eef93e92a4220af7849f6b26fff01",
            "component": {
              "name": "Copy",
              "options": {
                "rawHtml": "<h3>Programming Languages</h3><p>While Ethereum primarily uses Solidity for writing smart contracts, Solana uses <a href=\"https://solana.com/docs/programs/lang-rust\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Rust</a>. If moving from Ethereum, consider the <a href=\"https://www.anchor-lang.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Anchor framework</a> or <a href=\"https://neonevm.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Neon</a>, both of which can help developers get started faster by allowing them to build in Solana using familiar EVM tools.&nbsp;</p><p>Like Ethereum, there are <a href=\"https://solana.com/docs/clients/rust\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">client-side SDKs available</a> for many of the most popular programming languages, including <a href=\"https://github.com/solana-labs/solana-web3.js\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">JavaScript</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/michaelhly/solana-py\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Python</a>, and <a href=\"https://github.com/skynetcap/solanaj\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Java</a>.</p><h3>Developer Tooling</h3><p>Solana does not currently have an equivalent to Foundry, but it does have a wide set of tools equivalent to those used for Solidity.&nbsp;</p>"
              }
            },
